325adfdb-71d1-569e-a1b1-dba45a128d9c,tg:rubgr:2459,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"

(1527-1581, Master 1551). Attrib. to Martin van Cleve by Glück, Skating outside St. George's Gate in the same sense as Bruegel's drawing, not the engraving, but with many variations figures added and different spatial conception- exh. De Boer, Amsterdam: " De Helsche en de Fluweelen Brueghel", 1934, N° 108, pl. 19 in this exh. also by M. van Cleve; N° 107 Figure group pl. 30 signed with monogram & dated 1576; N° 109 "Bruiloftsmaal"; Exh. Vienna Gallerie St. Lucas "Die Jüngere Brueghel und ihr Kreis", 1935, Maerten van Cleve: 66 Das St. Martins'Feuer (beim Ausst. Wien 1930, N° 150 where repr.); 67 Eiertanz; 68 Brautzug; 69 Kindermord zu Bethlehem, Skizze nach der bekannten Komposition des Meisters; see also Denucé, Pelican (von der Osten-Vey, and Gerson).
